## 2026-03-28 - deleteTokenAtPath won't prune groups with only $-prefixed metadata keys
- Changed the empty-group check in `deleteTokenAtPath` from `Object.keys(child).length === 0` to `Object.keys(child).every(k => k.startsWith('$'))`, so groups containing only DTCG metadata keys ($type, $description, etc.) are pruned after the last real child token is deleted. The `every` check on an empty array still returns true, so truly empty groups continue to be pruned as before.
- Files changed: `packages/server/src/services/token-store.ts` ~L1191
- **Learnings for future iterations:**

